  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nBased on performance profiling done by @mandrigin , one of the worst culprits in bad app performance was realm-writing, which is made worse by the fact that we do every realm entity update as an distinct operation, so there is a lot more of app<->realm communication (and likely also realm communication over RNBridge) then needed.\r\nLuckily, we already reworked our persistence architecture to use async queues for all writes/updates, so only thing necessary is to batch those intelligently.\r\nWe can also use this opportunity to implement sort of basic \"transactions\", eq persistance operations put on queue by one `re-frame` event handler will be done, or none of them at all (capability which is currently lacking).",
